snippet.textDisplay:
@Rock Candy yes drugs will make someone in her position frame, gaslight and bait someone. Especially if she feels attacked and unstable. My sister is bipolar and is on cocaine.

One of the more recent things my sister had done to me was very conniving. My cat had gotten out and one of my neighbors had found him. He showed a picture of my cat to her and she sent him on a wild goose chase. She even drove around with this guy to "help him find my cats home" so yes drugs can make people do some of the most vial shit and it's not always in the heat of the moment. Drugs will cause people to plot and lie and create stories to gain sympathy.

I did eventually get my cat back. But it took weeks for the guy to find me because my sister sent him in the wrong direction.

Also we have both sides from court testimony and amber's "accidental" audio taping of the aftermath of the finger incident.  So there is A LOT of info out in the public - not everything but enough to understand the truth of innocence and guilt.
